141023f Auto-detect volatile columns during schema introspection
    This commit message section:
        A table with triggers has every column marked volatile (a trigger can
        touch any column), and the table is marked has_triggers, unless the
        table is declared no_volatile. Trigger detection is implemented for
        SQLite, PostgreSQL, and MySQL/MariaDB; DuckDB has no triggers.
    This is not what I wanted. Triggers do not cause all columns ot be
    volatile, it just adds the has_trigger meta-data to the table so that we
    get warning that some columns MAY be volatile, but that we could not detect
    it, that the user should either add no_volatile or mark specific columns as
    volatile based on the trigger, but that it cannot be done automatically.
